cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with semantic segmentation in drone videos, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions robot navigation and safety, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics). The proposed SegProp method involves iterative flow-based propagation, which is a machine learning technique and could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the lack of a large video aerial dataset, which could be addressed by using data augmentation techniques, falling under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the availability of a fast segmentation tool, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
